Package jmath.function

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Evaluable
    An interface which will be implemented by anything which could serve as an argument to an operation
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArgumentList
    Class representing an ordered list of arguments to a function
    ArithmeticOperation
    Class for objects representing arithmetic operations
    BinaryOperation
    Class for objects representing binary operations
    Equation
    Class for representing an equation or comparison between two expressions
    Expression
    A class whose objects represent a mathematical expression
    Function
    A class representing a parameterized function
    Operation
    A class from which all operations inherit.
    OperationFactory
    A static class for getting operations from the statically allocated operation space
    OperationSpace
    A class whose objects represent an available set of operations
    PieceWiseOperation
    Class for objects representing piece-wise operations
    Polynomial
    A class extending the functionality of jmath.function.Expression to allow for the handling of polynomials
    UnaryOperation
    Class for objects representing unary operations
    Value<T>
    Class whose objects represent the operable objects for parsed expressions
    Variable
    Objects of this class represent a variable for parsed expressions
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    EquationType
    An Enum for types of equations and comparisons
    EvaluableType
    An Enum for the available types of evaluables
    OperationType
    An Enum for types of operations for parsed expressions
    ValueType
    An Enum for the allowable value types for parsed expressions
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EvaluationException
    An exception class for exceptions related specifically to the evaluation of expressions
    OperationException
    An exception class for exceptions related specifically to the evaluation of operations
